{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f9ef062e-2a77-4479-80ab-9369bd4f56ff","content":"Two things changed with xUnit v3 + MTP:\n\n### 1. Filter syntax\n\nThe old VSTest `--filter` flag becomes `--filter` on the **MTP executable**, but the syntax is different:\n\n```bash\n# Old (VSTest / dotnet test with v2)\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n\n# New (MTP — the built executable is the test runner)\ndotnet run -- --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n#   or via dotnet test with the MTP bridge:\ndotnet test -- --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nNote the **`--`** separator — arguments after `--` are passed to the MTP runner. Without it, `dotnet test` interprets `--filter` as the old VSTest filter and it won't match.\n\n### 2. Trait filter syntax change\n\nIn MTP, trait filtering uses **`trait-name=value`** syntax instead of `Category=Smoke`:\n\n```bash\n# MTP filter (via dotnet test)\ndotnet test -- --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nThe `Category=Smoke` trait syntax is actually the same for xUnit v3 on MTP, but the key difference is the `--` separator.\n\n### TL;DR — your new CI command:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test -- --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nThe filter expression itself is unchanged; you just need the **`--`** before `--filter` so it's forwarded to the MTP runner instead of being consumed by `dotnet test` as a VSTest filter.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0b15a69e-30cd-472e-a834-1b1aa483b1e6","outputTokens":429,"requestId":"4C20:16C73:D8C3D2:10D95A2:6A012AEE"},"id":"b8bae004-2d13-4ae3-a54e-8b797ec77839","timestamp":"2026-05-11T01:03:52.419Z","parentId":"0a32fa5c-f521-490b-8b00-7f28ef3ac1cd"}
